%h2
  Iconv

%h2
  require "iconv" # => false ?!
%p
  If you have issues with iconv not being available in ruby / irb please try install the ruby you want with the following configure option:
%pre.code
  :preserve
    $ rvm package install iconv
    $ rvm remove 1.9.2
    $ rvm install 1.9.2 --with-iconv-dir=$rvm_path/usr

%p
  This effectively installs a fresh copy of iconv, sandboxed to the ~/.rvm/usr directory, and tells
  ruby to use it during the compile.
